We got the source as binary packages.  For example:

On Ubuntu based system:

  wget ftp://ftp.igd.fraunhofer.de/outgoing/irbuild/Ubuntu-x86_64/InstantReality-Ubuntu-14.04-x64-2.6.0.31123.deb


  and run: 'gdebi InstantReality-Ubuntu-14.04-x64-2.6.0.31123.deb'



  or

On redhat (centOS) based system:


  wget ftp://ftp.igd.fraunhofer.de/outgoing/irbuild/RedHat-7-x86_64/InstantReality-RedHat-7-x64-2.8.0.38807.rpm

  or

  firefox ftp://ftp.igd.fraunhofer.de/outgoing/irbuild/


   To install on CentOS 7:


   You may need to remove the old version via:


        yum remove InstantReality-bla-bla




        yum install InstantReality-RedHat-7-*.rpm

If if complains about an older version being in the way run:

        yum remove "OLDER_VERSION_THAT_YUM_INSTALL_SHOWED"

And try yum install again:


than:

        cp 2016_IR-license.xml /opt/instantReality/bin/license.xml


